# Catch — optional environment configuration.
#
# API keys are NOT stored here — enter them in the app's Settings (encrypted at
# rest via the OS keychain through Electron safeStorage). Provider base URLs and
# models are also chosen in Settings (including the "Custom" OpenAI-compatible
# provider). These env vars only cover the few things the UI can't.

# --- Azure OpenAI (required when using the "Azure OpenAI" provider) ---
# CATCH_AZURE_ENDPOINT=https://your-resource.openai.azure.com
# CATCH_AZURE_DEPLOYMENT=your-deployment-name
# CATCH_AZURE_API_VERSION=2024-06-01

# --- Obsidian export (optional) ---
# Target a specific vault; otherwise Obsidian's default vault is used.
# CATCH_OBSIDIAN_VAULT=My Vault

# --- Notion export (optional) ---
# Create an internal integration, share a parent page with it, then set:
# CATCH_NOTION_TOKEN=secret_xxx
# CATCH_NOTION_PARENT_PAGE_ID=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
